1) Launch instance as usual


2) sudo -i 
   sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get upgrade 

3) sudo apt install docker.io -y 

4) mkdir Docimage
5) cd Docimage
6) vi dockerfile 

7) Write a script --> :i (to insert) --> press esc:wq to exit 

FROM ubuntu 
MAINTAINER 20220801063@dypiu.ac.in
RUN apt-get update
RUN apt-get install -y nginx
CMD ["echo", "image created"]

8) cat dockerfile 

NOTE: Search Docker Hub on google and then login to the account using username and password
LOGIN USING GOOGLE
Click on Profile and note the username
Then go to password and change the password the link will be send on the respective email id

9) docker build -t image username/name:tag .    (docker build -t image mitali1512/mitali:tag .)

10) docker images

11) docker login  
(password won’t be visible but will show you “login succeeded”, it means you are into your account)  

12) docker push username/name:tag (docker push mitali1512/mitali:tag)

NOTE: Check in the Docker Hub A/C in repositories section 

13)  docker run username/name:tag  (docker run mitali1512/mitali:tag)

14) docker container ls -a

15) docker rm container-id  
